    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The third month of the year in the Julian and Gregorian calendars, containing 31 days and falling between February and April. It was named after Mars, the Roman god of war. Originally, March was the first month of the Roman calendar.</Note_Text>
